---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Masters">
  <p>Masters are reusable slide templates. Define them once and reference them from any slide, passing data to fill placeholders.</p>

  <h2>Defining a Master</h2>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">masters:
  title_slide:
    background: $primary
    elements:
      - type: text
        x: 0.8
        y: 1.2
        w: 8.4
        h: 2.2
        text: "&#123;&#123;title&#125;&#125;"
        font: $heading
        size: 44
        color: $white
        bold: true
        align: center
      - type: text
        x: 0.8
        y: 4.4
        w: 8.4
        h: 0.9
        text: "&#123;&#123;subtitle&#125;&#125;"
        size: 18
        color: $secondary
        align: center</code></pre>

  <h2>Placeholders</h2>
  <p>Use double curly braces <code>&#123;&#123;name&#125;&#125;</code> in any text value. When a slide uses this master, it passes a <code>data</code> object to fill them:</p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">slides:
  - master: title_slide
    data:
      title: "Q3 Performance Review"
      subtitle: "October 2025"</code></pre>

  <h2>Master Properties</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Key</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>background</code></td><td>string</td><td>Slide background color (hex or $variable)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>elements</code></td><td>array</td><td>List of elements on the master (same as slide elements)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Adding Slide-Specific Elements</h2>
  <p>A slide can use a master <em>and</em> add its own elements on top:</p>
  <pre><code class="language-yaml">slides:
  - master: content_slide
    data:
      title: "Key Metrics"
    elements:
      - type: chart
        chart: bar
        x: 0.5
        y: 1.5
        w: 9
        h: 3.5
        series:
          - name: "Revenue"
            labels: ["Q1", "Q2", "Q3"]
            values: [2800, 3200, 3700]</code></pre>
  <p>Master elements render first, then slide-specific elements layer on top.</p>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  th, td {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    text-align: left;
  }
  th {
    background: #f1f5f9;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
